In JIRA I can create a white header bar that has a 1px black border defined by "Header Separator Color". In Confluence there is also a border but that one always grabs the top bar background color (which makes not that much sense). On some pages it looks really weird to have a white top bar without separation. Unfortunately I can't really use another color than white for the top bar (CI/CD).

