The Page Properties Report macro produces useful tables of information, but the resulting table does not have a standard table header row, meaning it scrolls off-page unlike manually created tables. This is a major problem when multiple properties have the same possible values (e.g. "Low", "Medium", "High") and the report runs to many 10's of rows.

Could the page properties report inherit the same table style for it's headers (grey highlight, and doesn't scroll off-page) please? - Hopefully a minor fix that will have major benefit.

